newsitem.title: CYPRUS: Strong quake rocks Cyprus capital.
newsitem.headline: Strong quake rocks Cyprus capital.

text.p: A strong tremor shook the Cypriot capital Nicosia on Wednesday, shaking tall buildings, residents said.
The strong tremor lasted about a minute. Workers evacuated buildings in Nicosia. State radio said the tremor was felt across the Mediterranean island.
Police said they had no immediate information on damage. The seismological office was not immediately available.
The tremor also shook buildings in Cairo, some 400 miles (650 km) to the south.
